definition:
συν-αγωγή, -ῆς, ἡ 
 [in LXX chiefly for עֵדָה, also for קָהָל, etc. ;] 
prop., a bringing together; 
   1. of things, 
   (a) a gathering in of harvest; 
   (b) a collection of money. 
   2. Of persons, 
   (a) a collecting, assembling (Polyb.); 
   (b) an assembly (MM, xxiv; Deiss., LAE, 101 ff.): Rev.2:9 3:9; esp. of a Jewish religious assembly, a synagogue: Luk.12:11, Act.9:2, al.; of a Christian assembly, Jas.2:2. By meton., of the building in which the assembly is held, a synagogue: Mat.10:17, Mrk.1:21, al. (cf. Cremer, see word ἐκκλησία) 
 SYN.: ἐκκλησία (which see)  (AS)
